## Introduction
In this chapter youâ€™ll find a description of how to use images in Infinica templates. Open the *Palette *[`1: The Palette can be opened using the small arrow symbol on the top right of the Design window.`] and the *Outline *and *Properties View*.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

*Figure 3. Views of the Template Designer*

## Step by Step
Enter a new paragraph by either pressing ENTER while the cursor is in the *Design *window or drag a *Block *element from the *Palette *to the *Outline View*. Select an *Image *element in the Palette and drag it into the second block. Alternatively it is possible to double click the *Image *element while having the cursor at a valid position in the *Design *window.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

*Figure 4. Image element in the Palette*

As soon as the element has been inserted a placeholder is shown in the *Design *window. In order to assign an image, *double click *the placeholder and choose an image from the local

disc or enter a source path to *Properties &gt; Image *or *Advanced &gt; Miscellaneous &gt; src*. Please consider that the use of absolute paths is not recommended, in order to avoid that the image will not be found when the template is moved to another location. Having assigned an image, click to the tab *PDF (FOP)*, in order to create a PDF preview again.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

*Figure 5. Image placeholder*

## Things to Try
- Define the source path using *Properties &gt; Advanced &gt; Miscellaneous &gt; src*

- Experiment with the image dimension. This can be done *graphically *in the *Designer *window and *numeric *in the *properties *sheet, as well as with *uniform *and *non-uniform *scaling (*Properties &gt; Advanced &gt; Area Dimension &gt; scaling*).
